		"description": "<p>At 6th level, you learn to use sound not just as a tool, but as a weapon. As an action, you can emit a powerful blast of sound in a 15-foot cone. Creatures caught in the blast must make a Constitution&nbsp;save</span>&nbsp;against your&nbsp;spell save&nbsp;DC. On a failed saving throw, the target takes 2d8 thunder damage and is&nbsp;<span>deafened until the end of its next turn. On a success, the target takes half damage and isn&rsquo;t deafened. The damage increases to 3d8 at level 11. At 17th level, the damage increases to 4d8 and the blast becomes a 30-foot cone.</p>",
